Method 4: Install Podman Using a Pre-built VM (Podman Desktop)
Download Podman Desktop:

Visit Podman Desktop and download the latest version for Windows.
Install and Configure:

Run the installer and follow the setup instructions.
Podman Desktop will automatically configure a VM and provide a user interface for managing containers.
Use Podman via the GUI:

You can manage containers directly through the Podman Desktop GUI, similar to how you would with Docker Desktop.
